## Data Summary
This data comes [John Hopkins University](https://data.world/associatedpress/johns-hopkins-coronavirus-case-tracker/workspace/file?filename=1_county_level_confirmed_cases.csv) 
and it is a record of COVID-19 case and death data
from counties across the U.S. It contains numerical data on the number of COVID-19 cases 
and deaths reported by each county and also represents this data in comparison to the total
population of each county in the form of rate per 100,000 residents. The data represented below 
is a visualization of the confirmed COVID-19 deaths per county in the selected state.


[IdyllVegaLite data:cases spec:`{
  transform: [{filter:{field:"state", "equal":thestate}}],
  title: "Confirmed COVID-10 Cases For Counties in " + thestate,
  mark: "bar",
  width: 500,
  height: 1000,
  encoding: {
    x: {
      field: "deaths",
      type: "quantitative",
      title: "Number of Confirmed COVID-19 Deaths in Each County"
    },
    y: {
      field: "county_name",
      type: "ordinal",
      sort: "-x",
      title: "County Name"
    }
  }
}` 
